# AI Promptbook v2 – Cline / Roo Code Rules

## Project
Native desktop application for managing AI agent instructions, prompts, and project templates.
Stack: React 19 + TypeScript 5 + Vite 7 (frontend) | Rust + Tauri 2 (backend)

## Working directory layout
```
src/
  features/   one folder per page/route
  ui/         shared layout, components, theme
  services/   Tauri IPC and async operations
  state/      Zustand global stores
  domain/     pure TypeScript types and utilities
src-tauri/
  src/lib.rs  Rust Tauri commands (AES-256-GCM crypto)
  tauri.conf.json
  capabilities/
```

## Coding standards

### TypeScript
- Explicit types everywhere; `any` is not allowed
- Functional components + hooks only; no class components
- Shared state → Zustand store in `src/state/`
- All file I/O → `@tauri-apps/plugin-fs`
- GitHub tokens → always encrypt via `src/services/cryptoService.ts`
- Type-check: `tsc --noEmit`

### Rust
- Resolve all `clippy` warnings
- Command return type: `Result<T, String>`
- Keep crypto in `src-tauri/src/lib.rs`

## Useful commands
```bash
npm install           # install dependencies
npm run tauri dev     # start dev environment
tsc --noEmit          # type-check
```

## Constraints
- Do NOT use browser storage APIs (localStorage, sessionStorage, indexedDB)
- Do NOT expose secrets or tokens in plain text
- Do NOT bypass Tauri capability permissions
- Do NOT add packages without justification
